<Layout title="IUI - Intrauterine Insemination" description="Complete guide to IUI (intrauterine insemination) including the procedure, who it's for, success rates by age, costs, and what to expect during treatment.">
	<section class="hero-mini">
		<div class="container">
			<nav class="breadcrumb">
				<a href="/">Home</a>
				<span>‚Üí</span>
				<a href="/treatments/">Treatments</a>
				<span>‚Üí</span>
				<span>IUI</span>
			</nav>
			<h1>Intrauterine Insemination (IUI)</h1>
			<p>A fertility procedure that places prepared sperm directly into the uterus during ovulation.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="content-section">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="intro-box">
				<h2>What is IUI?</h2>
				<p>Intrauterine insemination (IUI), sometimes called artificial insemination, is a fertility treatment where concentrated, "washed" sperm is placed directly into the uterus through a thin catheter. This gives sperm a head start by bypassing the cervix and placing them closer to the egg.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="two-column-section">
				<div class="column">
					<div class="candidate-card good">
						<div class="card-header">
							<span class="icon">‚úì</span>
							<h3>IUI May Help With</h3>
						</div>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>Unexplained infertility</strong> ‚Äì No identified cause after testing</li>
							<li><strong>Mild male factor</strong> ‚Äì Slightly low sperm count or motility</li>
							<li><strong>Cervical factor</strong> ‚Äì Cervical mucus problems or scarring</li>
							<li><strong>Donor sperm</strong> ‚Äì Single parents or same-sex couples</li>
							<li><strong>Mild endometriosis</strong> ‚Äì Early-stage disease</li>
							<li><strong>Ovulatory dysfunction</strong> ‚Äì When combined with medications</li>
							<li><strong>Sexual dysfunction</strong> ‚Äì Difficulty with intercourse</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="column">
					<div class="candidate-card not-recommended">
						<div class="card-header">
							<span class="icon">‚úó</span>
							<h3>IUI NOT Recommended For</h3>
						</div>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>Blocked fallopian tubes</strong> ‚Äì Sperm cannot reach egg</li>
							<li><strong>Severe male factor</strong> ‚Äì Very low sperm count</li>
							<li><strong>Advanced endometriosis</strong> ‚Äì Stage III-IV disease</li>
							<li><strong>Pelvic infection history</strong> ‚Äì Risk of tubal damage</li>
						</ul>
						<div class="note">
							These conditions typically require IVF or other treatments.
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">The IUI Process</h2>

			<div class="process-timeline">
				<div class="process-step">
					<div class="step-number">1</div>
					<div class="step-content">
						<h3>Ovarian Stimulation <span class="optional-badge">Optional</span></h3>
						<p>IUI can be done with natural ovulation or with medications to stimulate egg production:</p>
						<div class="step-options">
							<div class="option">
								<strong>Natural Cycle IUI</strong>
								<span>Uses your natural ovulation</span>
							</div>
							<div class="option">
								<strong>Medicated IUI</strong>
								<span>Clomid, letrozole, or injectables to produce 1-3 eggs</span>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="process-step">
					<div class="step-number">2</div>
					<div class="step-content">
						<h3>Monitoring</h3>
						<div class="monitoring-items">
							<div class="monitoring-item">
								<span class="icon">üìä</span>
								<span>Ultrasound to track follicle growth</span>
							</div>
							<div class="monitoring-item">
								<span class="icon">ü©∏</span>
								<span>Blood tests for hormone levels</span>
							</div>
							<div class="monitoring-item">
								<span class="icon">üè†</span>
								<span>Ovulation predictor kits at home</span>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="process-step">
					<div class="step-number">3</div>
					<div class="step-content">
						<h3>Trigger Shot <span class="common-badge">Often Used</span></h3>
						<p>An hCG injection to trigger ovulation, ensuring precise timing of the IUI procedure approximately 36 hours later.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="process-step">
					<div class="step-number">4</div>
					<div class="step-content">
						<h3>Sperm Preparation</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>Sperm sample collected 1-2 hours before procedure</li>
							<li>"Washing" separates healthy, motile sperm from semen</li>
							<li>Concentrated sperm prepared in small volume (~0.5ml)</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="process-step">
					<div class="step-number">5</div>
					<div class="step-content">
						<h3>Insemination Procedure</h3>
						<div class="procedure-details">
							<div class="detail-item">
								<span class="label">Duration</span>
								<span class="value">5-10 minutes</span>
							</div>
							<div class="detail-item">
								<span class="label">Pain level</span>
								<span class="value">Similar to Pap smear</span>
							</div>
							<div class="detail-item">
								<span class="label">Anesthesia</span>
								<span class="value">Not required</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<p>Thin catheter inserted through cervix, sperm deposited directly into uterus.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="process-step">
					<div class="step-number">6</div>
					<div class="step-content">
						<h3>Two-Week Wait</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>Progesterone support sometimes prescribed</li>
							<li>Pregnancy test 14 days after IUI</li>
							<li>Blood hCG test to confirm pregnancy</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Success Rates</h2>

			<div class="stats-highlight">
				<div class="stat-card primary">
					<div class="stat-value">10.9%</div>
					<div class="stat-label">Live birth rate per cycle</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-card">
					<div class="stat-value">19.4%</div>
					<div class="stat-label">Across multiple cycles</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-card">
					<div class="stat-value">~40%</div>
					<div class="stat-label">Within 3 cycles (under 35)</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="table-container">
				<table class="styled-table">
					<thead>
						<tr>
							<th>Protocol</th>
							<th>Success Rate Per Cycle</th>
						</tr>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr>
							<td>Natural cycle IUI</td>
							<td><span class="rate low">5-10%</span></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td>Clomid/Letrozole + IUI</td>
							<td><span class="rate moderate">10-15%</span></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td>Injectable medications + IUI</td>
							<td><span class="rate good">15-20%</span></td>
						</tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>

			<div class="table-container">
				<table class="styled-table">
					<thead>
						<tr>
							<th>Age Group</th>
							<th>Success Rate Per Cycle</th>
						</tr>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr>
							<td>Under 35</td>
							<td><span class="rate good">15-20%</span></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td>35-40</td>
							<td><span class="rate moderate">10-15%</span></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td>Over 40</td>
							<td><span class="rate low">5-10%</span></td>
						</tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>

			<div class="comparison-box">
				<h3>IUI vs. IVF: What the Research Shows</h3>
				<p>For unexplained infertility, comparing immediate IVF vs. IUI:</p>
				<div class="comparison-stats">
					<div class="comparison-item ivf">
						<span class="treatment">IVF</span>
						<span class="result">49% pregnancy rate</span>
						<span class="note">in first 2 cycles</span>
					</div>
					<div class="comparison-item iui">
						<span class="treatment">IUI + Clomid</span>
						<span class="result">21.6% pregnancy rate</span>
					</div>
					<div class="comparison-item iui">
						<span class="treatment">IUI + Injectables</span>
						<span class="result">17.3% pregnancy rate</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p class="comparison-conclusion">IVF delivers 2-10x higher live birth rates but at significantly higher cost per cycle.</p>
				<p class="citation">Sources: <a href="https://www.fertilityiq.com/fertilityiq/iui-or-artificial-insemination/how-well-iui-works-by-patient-type" target="_blank" rel="noopener">FertilityIQ</a>, <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8769183/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PMC - IVF vs IUI Comparative Analysis</a></p>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Costs</h2>

			<div class="cost-breakdown">
				<div class="cost-category">
					<h3>Base IUI Costs</h3>
					<div class="cost-items">
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="item-name">IUI procedure only</span>
							<span class="item-cost">$300-$1,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="item-name">Monitoring (ultrasounds, bloodwork)</span>
							<span class="item-cost">$200-$500</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="item-name">Sperm wash/prep</span>
							<span class="item-cost">$150-$400</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="item-name">Trigger shot</span>
							<span class="item-cost">$50-$200</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="cost-category">
					<h3>Medication Options</h3>
					<div class="cost-items">
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="item-name">Oral medications (Clomid/Letrozole)</span>
							<span class="item-cost">$10-$150</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="item-name">Injectable medications</span>
							<span class="item-cost">$1,500-$5,000</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="total-cost-cards">
				<div class="total-card">
					<div class="total-label">Natural/Oral Med IUI</div>
					<div class="total-amount">$500-$2,000</div>
					<div class="total-note">per cycle</div>
				</div>
				<div class="total-card highlighted">
					<div class="total-label">Injectable IUI</div>
					<div class="total-amount">$2,500-$7,000</div>
					<div class="total-note">per cycle</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="addon-box">
				<h3>Using Donor Sperm?</h3>
				<p>Add these costs:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Donor sperm vial:</strong> $500-$1,200</li>
					<li><strong>Shipping:</strong> $200-$400</li>
					<li><strong>Storage fees:</strong> varies by sperm bank</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Risks & Side Effects</h2>

			<div class="risks-grid">
				<div class="risk-card common">
					<div class="risk-header">
						<span class="severity">Common</span>
					</div>
					<h4>Cramping</h4>
					<p>Mild discomfort during or after the procedure</p>
				</div>
				<div class="risk-card common">
					<div class="risk-header">
						<span class="severity">Common</span>
					</div>
					<h4>Spotting</h4>
					<p>Light bleeding is normal and temporary</p>
				</div>
				<div class="risk-card moderate">
					<div class="risk-header">
						<span class="severity">10-20% with meds</span>
					</div>
					<h4>Multiple Pregnancy</h4>
					<p>Usually twins when using medications</p>
				</div>
				<div class="risk-card rare">
					<div class="risk-header">
						<span class="severity">Rare</span>
					</div>
					<h4>Infection</h4>
					<p>Very rare (&lt;0.1% of procedures)</p>
				</div>
				<div class="risk-card rare">
					<div class="risk-header">
						<span class="severity">Rare with oral meds</span>
					</div>
					<h4>OHSS</h4>
					<p>Possible with injectables</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">How Many Cycles?</h2>

			<div class="recommendation-box">
				<div class="recommendation">
					<div class="rec-number">3-4</div>
					<div class="rec-text">
						<strong>Recommended cycles</strong>
						<span>before moving to IVF</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="recommendation">
					<div class="rec-number">6</div>
					<div class="rec-text">
						<strong>Maximum cycles</strong>
						<span>Success unlikely beyond this</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="callout-box warning">
				<div class="callout-icon">‚ö°</div>
				<div class="callout-content">
					<h4>When to Consider IVF Instead</h4>
					<p>If you're over 38, have been trying for 2+ years, have diminished ovarian reserve, or have a diagnosis that makes IUI unlikely to work, your doctor may recommend proceeding directly to IVF.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Questions to Ask Your Doctor</h2>

			<div class="questions-list">
				<div class="question-item">
					<span class="q-icon">?</span>
					<span>What's my estimated success rate based on my specific diagnosis?</span>
				</div>
				<div class="question-item">
					<span class="q-icon">?</span>
					<span>Should I use medications with IUI or try natural cycle first?</span>
				</div>
				<div class="question-item">
					<span class="q-icon">?</span>
					<span>How many IUI cycles do you recommend before moving to IVF?</span>
				</div>
				<div class="question-item">
					<span class="q-icon">?</span>
					<span>What does your clinic's IUI success rate look like for patients like me?</span>
				</div>
			</div>

			<nav class="nav-footer">
				<a href="/treatments/medication/" class="nav-prev">
					<span class="nav-label">Previous</span>
					<span class="nav-title">‚Üê Medication</span>
				</a>
				<a href="/treatments/ivf/" class="nav-next">
					<span class="nav-label">Next</span>
					<span class="nav-title">IVF ‚Üí</span>
				</a>
			</nav>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

